# BuildY — UI structure

Minimal app shell with the **full `internal/ui` registry tree** for staging reusable UI.
On-disk index: **`internal/ui/README.md`** (same `registry:*` labels as FastyGoUI).

```
internal/ui/
  layout/       # registry:layout — shell, header, footer, mobile sheet
  components/   # registry:components — icon, toggles, …
  blocks/       # registry:blocks — dashboard/, marketing/, docs/ (staging)
  widgets/      # registry:widgets — UI + behavior (staging)
  variants/     # registry:variants — wireframe utility maps
  utils/        # registry:utils — app helpers on templ/utils
internal/views/
  *.templ       # route pages (home hero, sample, …)
  partials/     # shell head assets, header trailing glue
  models.go     # LayoutData, page structs
internal/site/
  feature.go    # routes, locale wiring, static nav
internal/fixtures/
  locale/*.json # i18n copy
```

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `internal/ui/layout` | App chrome; stays in app after extraction |
| `internal/ui/components` | Props-only UI; no HTTP or fetch |
| `internal/ui/blocks/<group>` | Section organisms → future `fastygo/blocks` |
| `internal/ui/widgets` | Behavior shells → future `fastygo/widgets` |
| `internal/views` | Compose layout + resolved fixture strings |

**views** receive resolved strings/structs only — no `fixtures.LoadLocale` inside `.templ`.

When adding a page: extend `fixtures.Locale` + every `locale/*.json`, add nav in `site/feature.go`, add `internal/views/<page>.templ`, register route in `site/feature.go`.

For sidebar layout, see git branch **`sidebar`**.
